title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\VpnGatewayStatusHighAvailabilityRequirementState
name: VpnGatewayStatusHighAvailabilityRequirementState
description:
Describes the high availability requirement state for the VPN connection between this Cloud VPN gateway and a peer gateway.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.compute.v1.VpnGatewayStatusHighAvailabilityRequirementState

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.state
params.description: Indicates the high availability requirement state for the VPN connection. Valid values are CONNECTION_REDUNDANCY_MET, CONNECTION_REDUNDANCY_NOT_MET. Check the State enum for the list of possible values.

params.name: data.unsatisfied_reason
params.description: Indicates the reason why the VPN connection does not meet the high availability redundancy criteria/requirement. Valid values is INCOMPLETE_TUNNELS_COVERAGE. Check the UnsatisfiedReason enum for the list of possible values.
